<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>29-1303.04</num>
  <heading>Benefit officer.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>A benefit corporation may designate a benefit officer.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>A benefit officer shall have:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>The powers and duties relating to the purpose of the corporation to create general public benefit or specific public benefit provided:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(A)</num>
        <text>By the bylaws; or</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(B)</num>
        <text>Absent controlling provisions in the bylaws, by resolutions or orders of the board of directors; and</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>The duty to prepare the benefit report required by <cite path="§29-1304.01">§ 29-1304.01</cite>.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 19-305" type="History">May 1, 2013, D.C. Law 19-305, § 2(b), 60 DCR 2735</annotation>
    <annotation type="Section References">This section is referenced in <cite path="§29-1301.02">§ 29-1301.02</cite>.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
